1
00:00:39,075 --> 00:00:40,545
(All characters, places,
and organizations are fictional.)

2
00:00:40,545 --> 00:00:41,975
(Children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

3
00:00:44,285 --> 00:00:46,215
(Episode 15)

4
00:01:02,365 --> 00:01:03,465
(Missed Call)

5
00:01:03,535 --> 00:01:04,635
(New Message)

6
00:01:04,705 --> 00:01:05,775
(Missed Call)

7
00:01:05,835 --> 00:01:06,975
(New Message)

8
00:01:07,035 --> 00:01:08,175
(New Message)

9
00:01:13,915 --> 00:01:15,075
(Messages)

10
00:01:16,515 --> 00:01:18,385
(Director Shin, please text me
when you have a moment. Ba Ra.)

11
00:01:21,255 --> 00:01:24,625
Director Shin, please text me
when you have a moment.

12
00:01:25,185 --> 00:01:26,195
Ba Ra.

13
00:01:32,735 --> 00:01:34,195
Hello, Director Shin.

14
00:01:35,765 --> 00:01:38,305
- Where are you?
- I'm at the cafe by the hospital.

15
00:01:39,235 --> 00:01:42,145
- You're at the cafe now?
- Yes. But...

16
00:01:42,845 --> 00:01:46,615
I'd like to meet somewhere quiet.
It's a little noisy here.

17
00:01:47,215 --> 00:01:49,515
Go on up to my place.
The door code is the same.

18
00:01:52,985 --> 00:01:55,055
Did you forget? Want me to text it to you?

19
00:01:55,685 --> 00:01:56,685
No.

20
00:02:20,715 --> 00:02:21,775
You've been in Korea?

21
00:02:22,415 --> 00:02:24,215
- Yes.
- But...

22
00:02:25,855 --> 00:02:26,855
where?

23
00:02:30,555 --> 00:02:31,625
I'll order something.

24
00:02:32,595 --> 00:02:33,695
You haven't had dinner, have you?

25
00:02:34,155 --> 00:02:35,355
I'm not hungry.

26
00:02:38,125 --> 00:02:39,795
Should I make you something simple?

27
00:02:52,075 --> 00:02:53,075
Did you get married?

28
00:02:53,945 --> 00:02:54,945
No.

29
00:02:55,785 --> 00:02:58,915
(Someone said they saw you...)

30
00:03:01,885 --> 00:03:03,585
About the surgery you mentioned before...

31
00:03:05,525 --> 00:03:06,525
I'll do it.

32
00:03:07,355 --> 00:03:08,355
Please do it for me.

33
00:03:17,235 --> 00:03:18,435
Do you want me to explain why?

34
00:03:19,405 --> 00:03:20,975
- Change?
- Yes.

35
00:03:25,105 --> 00:03:27,845
- Momo might not agree to it.
- Even if she doesn't.

36
00:03:31,915 --> 00:03:33,085
I'll take full responsibility.

37
00:03:38,285 --> 00:03:39,455
Are you not up for it?

38
00:03:54,905 --> 00:03:55,905
All right.

39
00:04:03,585 --> 00:04:06,215
(Nua General Hospital)

40
00:04:31,345 --> 00:04:32,345
Have a seat.

41
00:04:44,985 --> 00:04:46,095
I rushed over...

42
00:04:46,825 --> 00:04:47,825
empty-handed.

43
00:04:51,165 --> 00:04:52,165
Are you okay?

44
00:04:53,565 --> 00:04:57,205
I just had a dizzy spell.

45
00:05:03,845 --> 00:05:05,205
You still look good.

46
00:05:05,745 --> 00:05:06,745
I do?

47
00:05:08,575 --> 00:05:11,445
I saw Momo. She said she's happy.

48
00:05:13,115 --> 00:05:15,725
Except that you're
a bit too obsessed with her.

49
00:05:19,825 --> 00:05:21,125
That's why she's deliberately...

50
00:05:23,025 --> 00:05:24,825
keeping her distance for a while.

51
00:05:26,535 --> 00:05:27,735
We decided to get a divorce.

52
00:05:29,165 --> 00:05:30,165
We're going to.

53
00:05:33,635 --> 00:05:35,405
How could you just leave like that?

54
00:05:39,475 --> 00:05:41,875
- Vertigo?
- I have a blood test tomorrow.

55
00:05:42,415 --> 00:05:43,715
They think it might be anemia.

56
00:05:44,385 --> 00:05:45,415
So you have to fast tonight?

57
00:05:47,355 --> 00:05:48,685
I'm not really that hungry.

58
00:05:49,655 --> 00:05:50,655
Why are you being so formal?

59
00:05:52,285 --> 00:05:53,755
You're not even looking at me.

60
00:06:02,195 --> 00:06:03,365
Did something happen?

61
00:06:07,035 --> 00:06:08,035
No.

62
00:06:09,375 --> 00:06:10,375
Someone...

63
00:06:11,245 --> 00:06:13,145
said they saw you at a rest stop.

64
00:06:13,815 --> 00:06:15,145
You were with an elderly woman.

65
00:06:17,615 --> 00:06:18,815
That was probably me.

66
00:06:23,655 --> 00:06:24,755
Did you meet someone?

67
00:06:29,865 --> 00:06:31,765
I said I needed time back then.

68
00:06:33,895 --> 00:06:35,695
Time to force feelings for you?

69
00:06:35,765 --> 00:06:37,205
I wasn't forcing it.

70
00:06:41,975 --> 00:06:43,305
Will you keep on staying at a distance?

71
00:06:50,845 --> 00:06:52,145
My feelings haven't changed.

72
00:06:56,225 --> 00:06:57,325
Nothing's changed.

73
00:07:02,925 --> 00:07:04,225
We should have been honest...

74
00:07:05,495 --> 00:07:07,165
and talked everything out sooner.

75
00:07:14,075 --> 00:07:16,275
- What about a caregiver?
- I don't need one.

76
00:07:17,205 --> 00:07:18,775
I can still get around on my own.

77
00:07:18,845 --> 00:07:19,875
Then I'll stay with you.

78
00:07:19,875 --> 00:07:21,845
As Momo's world-famous husband?

79
00:07:24,585 --> 00:07:25,715
You're angry with me,

80
00:07:26,455 --> 00:07:27,515
aren't you?

81
00:07:31,525 --> 00:07:33,195
I lost sight of the young girl
you used to be.

82
00:07:34,195 --> 00:07:35,925
I didn't even make an effort.

83
00:07:39,095 --> 00:07:40,365
Please, stop being upset.

84
00:07:44,805 --> 00:07:46,075
I'm here to check your blood pressure.

85
00:07:46,775 --> 00:07:47,835
You can go now.

86
00:07:53,415 --> 00:07:54,415
Your number.

87
00:08:15,195 --> 00:08:17,665
I'll do anything to convince Ba Ra,

88
00:08:17,935 --> 00:08:19,305
so please do the surgery again.

89
00:08:20,135 --> 00:08:22,475
Just turn me into Ba Ra,
and then we can get married.

90
00:08:24,775 --> 00:08:26,375
Ba Ra showed up today.

91
00:08:27,315 --> 00:08:28,315
I met her.

92
00:08:29,545 --> 00:08:30,545
What did she say?

93
00:08:34,115 --> 00:08:35,715
I'll have ten kids
if that's what it takes.

94
00:08:36,325 --> 00:08:37,325
As many as we can have.

95
00:08:39,595 --> 00:08:42,925
I know Ba Ra,
and Yong Joong is the only one for her.

96
00:08:43,265 --> 00:08:45,465
And after Geum Ba Ra disappeared,

97
00:08:45,795 --> 00:08:47,695
Ha Yong Joong couldn't stop
thinking about her either.

98
00:08:48,435 --> 00:08:50,705
We don't have to live as a couple
in name only anymore.

99
00:08:58,245 --> 00:09:00,475
I want to do something good for once.

100
00:09:03,685 --> 00:09:06,455
Ba Ra can become Momo
and marry Yong Joong,

101
00:09:06,755 --> 00:09:08,185
and I'll become Ba Ra...

102
00:09:08,185 --> 00:09:11,585
and live my life
admiring and devoted to you.

103
00:09:12,625 --> 00:09:14,455
I'll study hard to become
more cultured and refined.

104
00:09:18,525 --> 00:09:19,765
It's a win-win for everyone.

105
00:09:24,505 --> 00:09:25,605
Discuss it with Ba Ra.

106
00:09:27,705 --> 00:09:28,835
If she agrees to switch,

107
00:09:29,475 --> 00:09:30,505
will you really do it?

108
00:09:39,045 --> 00:09:41,615
I can put everything I just said
in writing as a pledge.

109
00:09:46,625 --> 00:09:48,195
The truth is,
the news articles were right.

110
00:09:49,625 --> 00:09:51,195
Things aren't good
between Yong Joong and me.

111
00:09:51,765 --> 00:09:53,395
I just pretended
we were fine out of pride.

112
00:09:55,235 --> 00:09:59,035
Think about becoming Momo
and marrying Yong Joong.

113
00:10:03,475 --> 00:10:06,515
And I could become you
and live as Geum Ba Ra.

114
00:10:08,275 --> 00:10:11,615
And I could become you
and live as Geum Ba Ra.

115
00:10:13,615 --> 00:10:16,225
Director Shin said he'd do the surgery
if you agreed.

116
00:10:17,325 --> 00:10:19,895
You'll get wealth, fame, and even love,

117
00:10:20,295 --> 00:10:22,795
all from a surgery that takes a few hours.

118
00:10:26,095 --> 00:10:29,435
Director Shin is an amazing surgeon.

119
00:10:29,835 --> 00:10:31,505
I was completely blown away.

120
00:10:34,505 --> 00:10:37,875
No matter how good Director Shin is to you
or how hard he tries,

121
00:10:38,045 --> 00:10:40,315
you have no intention
of marrying him, right?

122
00:10:41,915 --> 00:10:45,085
Honestly, don't you feel a little bad
for Director Shin?

123
00:10:45,885 --> 00:10:48,785
He seems to have it all,
but when you really think about it,

124
00:10:49,055 --> 00:10:50,525
does he have time to spend his money?

125
00:10:50,585 --> 00:10:52,385
Or does he really have
any hobbies he enjoys?

126
00:10:52,625 --> 00:10:55,555
He's in this hospital 24 hours a day,

127
00:10:55,655 --> 00:10:58,725
either in the OR, his office,
or a patient's room.

128
00:10:59,735 --> 00:11:03,065
If I became you
and married Director Shin...

129
00:11:03,665 --> 00:11:05,835
and then dedicated my life
to taking proper care of him,

130
00:11:06,605 --> 00:11:08,135
wouldn't that give you
more peace of mind, too?

131
00:11:12,675 --> 00:11:14,945
Why did things go bad
between you and Yong Joong?

132
00:11:17,045 --> 00:11:18,415
A little bit of everything, I guess.

133
00:11:18,885 --> 00:11:20,155
We're completely incompatible,

134
00:11:20,215 --> 00:11:21,355
right down to our tastes.

135
00:11:22,115 --> 00:11:23,885
I think he was just Momo's fan.

136
00:11:25,255 --> 00:11:27,325
You're sick and tired of your life, too,
aren't you?

137
00:11:28,525 --> 00:11:31,265
Think of the discrimination and neglect
we grew up with.

138
00:11:33,665 --> 00:11:35,265
Don't you have any intention
of apologizing to me?

139
00:11:38,605 --> 00:11:39,635
Not even now?

140
00:11:44,345 --> 00:11:45,345
For what?

141
00:11:46,175 --> 00:11:48,015
I want an apology. A proper one.

142
00:11:49,415 --> 00:11:50,485
I deserve one.

143
00:11:56,185 --> 00:11:58,755
My life could have been so much better
if it weren't for you.

144
00:11:59,925 --> 00:12:01,555
But you ruined everything.

145
00:12:02,325 --> 00:12:03,825
By framing me for theft.

146
00:12:05,925 --> 00:12:09,165
Even now, my chest gets tight
just thinking about it.

147
00:12:09,835 --> 00:12:10,835
If you were in my shoes,

148
00:12:11,605 --> 00:12:13,475
how would you have felt
if I'd done that to you?

149
00:12:20,545 --> 00:12:21,575
I'm sorry.

150
00:12:22,345 --> 00:12:24,415
I kept hoping
you would apologize eventually.

151
00:12:25,785 --> 00:12:29,085
Since we were both left in the baby box
on the same day and grew up together,

152
00:12:29,085 --> 00:12:30,385
I decided to just let it slide.

153
00:12:32,425 --> 00:12:33,925
But you acted like nothing ever happened.

154
00:12:35,455 --> 00:12:37,325
You weren't the Kim Jin Ju
I thought I knew.

155
00:12:38,625 --> 00:12:40,635
I don't know how a person
could do something like that.

156
00:12:41,865 --> 00:12:43,905
You act nice, then stab me in the back.

157
00:12:43,905 --> 00:12:45,365
I didn't stab you in the back.

158
00:12:45,365 --> 00:12:46,375
You didn't?

159
00:12:51,805 --> 00:12:53,645
My circumstances made me that way.

160
00:12:56,145 --> 00:12:57,885
- You don't get it?
- No.

161
00:12:58,215 --> 00:13:00,055
We had the exact same circumstances.

162
00:13:01,315 --> 00:13:04,325
That's because you're smart.

163
00:13:04,385 --> 00:13:07,355
This isn't about being smart.
It's about having a conscience.

164
00:13:10,965 --> 00:13:13,795
You ended up fine even though
Ye Jeong's family didn't adopt you.

165
00:13:14,295 --> 00:13:16,505
But I was more heartbroken
than anyone else.

166
00:13:17,165 --> 00:13:20,305
To be betrayed by you, of all people.

167
00:13:22,005 --> 00:13:23,905
But I paid for it in the end.

168
00:13:25,505 --> 00:13:26,845
I was wrong.

169
00:13:28,175 --> 00:13:29,175
I'm sorry.

170
00:13:33,015 --> 00:13:35,155
Deep down, I was always sorry.

171
00:13:36,585 --> 00:13:38,685
But you were always so cold to me,

172
00:13:39,925 --> 00:13:41,325
I could never bring myself to say it.

173
00:13:42,195 --> 00:13:44,295
Living as Momo can't be that bad.

174
00:13:45,565 --> 00:13:46,695
So what if you get divorced?

175
00:13:47,465 --> 00:13:50,465
You can meet any rich, famous guy
you want.

176
00:13:52,165 --> 00:13:53,435
Why do you want to become me?

177
00:13:56,175 --> 00:13:57,175
My pride.

178
00:13:58,705 --> 00:14:00,645
Everyone would love to see me fail,
wouldn't they?

179
00:14:01,415 --> 00:14:02,775
The haters, the reporters...

180
00:14:03,845 --> 00:14:06,255
You know how many reporters
can't stand Momo.

181
00:14:06,385 --> 00:14:09,115
You'd do the surgery again just for that?

182
00:14:09,285 --> 00:14:10,825
It's only the first step that's hard.

183
00:14:11,085 --> 00:14:13,025
You're just asleep for a few hours,
and then you wake up.

184
00:14:13,555 --> 00:14:14,625
It's no big deal.

185
00:14:18,595 --> 00:14:20,695
Try living as Momo for a while.

186
00:14:21,265 --> 00:14:22,795
Spending money is a lot of fun, too.

187
00:14:23,335 --> 00:14:24,435
It's beyond your wildest dreams.

188
00:14:27,235 --> 00:14:31,805
There's no reason
to cling to that face and body.

189
00:14:33,615 --> 00:14:36,445
Think of all the tears you've shed
with those eyes.

190
00:14:37,845 --> 00:14:40,785
Fate gives everyone a few chances in life.

191
00:14:40,785 --> 00:14:42,415
Think of this as one of them.

192
00:14:43,355 --> 00:14:47,355
Ever since you disappeared,
I've lived with a shell of Ha Yong Joong.

193
00:14:47,925 --> 00:14:50,025
I can't do it anymore.
I'm sick and tired of it.

194
00:14:52,095 --> 00:14:54,195
Director Shin might seem cold
on the outside,

195
00:14:55,095 --> 00:14:57,565
but he's better than the empty shell
Ha Yong Joong has become.

196
00:14:57,835 --> 00:14:59,005
Even if he only wants Ba Ra's body.

197
00:15:01,305 --> 00:15:02,945
It's about choosing the next-best thing.

198
00:15:02,945 --> 00:15:04,845
That's what Director Shin is doing.

199
00:15:05,305 --> 00:15:07,375
And Ha Yong Joong
has to pay the price, too.

200
00:15:08,015 --> 00:15:12,385
He doesn't deserve to marry the real you.
Didn't he just end up hurting us both?

201
00:15:12,885 --> 00:15:14,515
He should've chosen you from the start.

202
00:15:18,755 --> 00:15:20,095
Do you need some time to think?

203
00:15:26,865 --> 00:15:28,465
I should've listened to you.

204
00:15:29,865 --> 00:15:31,365
There's no turning back now.

205
00:15:31,565 --> 00:15:34,205
Everyone makes mistakes. We're human.

206
00:15:34,475 --> 00:15:35,935
Just as long as you don't repeat them.

207
00:15:36,445 --> 00:15:38,275
Chalk it up to a life lesson.

208
00:15:42,345 --> 00:15:43,515
By the way,

209
00:15:43,785 --> 00:15:45,645
Momo is a world-class liar.

210
00:15:46,185 --> 00:15:48,015
Saying she was abused growing up?

211
00:15:49,415 --> 00:15:50,885
Just what you'd expect from an actress.

212
00:15:51,785 --> 00:15:52,855
Hyun Ran Hee.

213
00:15:53,355 --> 00:15:56,495
After her first love,
Paul, the artist, came to Korea,

214
00:15:56,495 --> 00:15:58,425
she found out
she had lost her own daughter.

215
00:15:59,165 --> 00:16:00,665
So what's all this about abuse?

216
00:16:01,295 --> 00:16:03,865
She thought her daughter was living well
in Japan with Paul.

217
00:16:06,335 --> 00:16:07,535
I'm going to finalize the paperwork,

218
00:16:09,075 --> 00:16:10,345
and then I'm going to marry Ba Ra.

219
00:16:12,375 --> 00:16:13,715
You found Reporter Geum?

220
00:16:14,245 --> 00:16:18,085
Please check the baby's diaper often.
The baby is very sensitive.

221
00:16:23,725 --> 00:16:25,785
Is Grandmother still eating well?

222
00:16:28,225 --> 00:16:31,625
She especially likes hairtail,
so make sure to debone it well for her.

223
00:16:34,765 --> 00:16:35,765
Okay.

224
00:16:36,265 --> 00:16:37,905
Her hemoglobin levels are a bit low,

225
00:16:38,665 --> 00:16:40,275
but that can happen to women
because of their period.

226
00:16:40,975 --> 00:16:43,075
But just in case,
I've scheduled an MRI this weekend.

227
00:16:43,245 --> 00:16:45,145
Does she just need to eat well?
Things like meat?

228
00:16:46,645 --> 00:16:48,045
Well, she's on an albumin drip for now.

229
00:16:50,785 --> 00:16:51,915
Did she say anything else?

230
00:16:52,745 --> 00:16:54,155
Like how she's been?

231
00:16:55,155 --> 00:16:56,425
She'll talk when she's ready.

232
00:16:59,685 --> 00:17:00,695
(Ready for surgery)

233
00:17:00,855 --> 00:17:02,025
I have to go into surgery.

234
00:17:08,135 --> 00:17:09,835
(No Visitors Permitted,
Please inquire at the nurses' station.)

235
00:17:25,085 --> 00:17:26,215
It says no visitors.

236
00:17:47,205 --> 00:17:49,375
Let's finalize everything in six months.

237
00:17:50,445 --> 00:17:52,475
That's if you haven't changed
your mind by then.

238
00:17:54,275 --> 00:17:57,345
I know I haven't been my best self.

239
00:17:57,615 --> 00:17:59,685
I've been on edge
and took it out on you a lot.

240
00:18:02,685 --> 00:18:04,055
I know I didn't live up to
your expectations.

241
00:18:06,125 --> 00:18:09,155
I just want to stay your wife
for a few more months,

242
00:18:09,825 --> 00:18:10,925
even if it's only on paper.

243
00:18:12,265 --> 00:18:15,135
You don't have to give me alimony.
I didn't mean what I said.

244
00:18:17,565 --> 00:18:19,465
I know money can't make up for it,

245
00:18:20,835 --> 00:18:21,975
but you should take what you're owed.

246
00:18:24,075 --> 00:18:27,645
If I hadn't had the miscarriage,
we probably would've just made it work.

247
00:18:32,445 --> 00:18:33,785
I'll get the rest of my stuff tomorrow.

248
00:18:38,185 --> 00:18:40,325
Ask Geum Ba Ra if she was really pregnant.

249
00:18:40,825 --> 00:18:42,495
Someone saw her, and you can't even ask?

250
00:18:55,235 --> 00:18:56,235
Are you sleeping?

251
00:19:22,065 --> 00:19:23,065
(New Message)

252
00:19:31,605 --> 00:19:33,075
Can we meet tomorrow?

253
00:19:33,475 --> 00:19:35,615
I can't eat since I'm fasting.

254
00:19:50,695 --> 00:19:52,125
Like Director Shin said,

255
00:19:53,395 --> 00:19:55,095
it's true that
I used to have feelings for you.

256
00:19:56,705 --> 00:20:00,505
When I was younger,
I just liked you because you doted on me.

257
00:20:05,805 --> 00:20:08,475
I guess feelings are like the wind.

258
00:20:09,715 --> 00:20:11,045
Over the past year,

259
00:20:12,085 --> 00:20:13,515
those feelings have faded.

260
00:20:14,015 --> 00:20:15,415
All that was left behind
were the memories.

261
00:20:16,825 --> 00:20:17,985
The good ones.

262
00:20:18,755 --> 00:20:20,625
You've given me so many.

263
00:20:20,755 --> 00:20:22,255
We made them together.

264
00:20:23,865 --> 00:20:25,065
Now, I'm the one...

265
00:20:25,665 --> 00:20:27,635
who's going to like you much more.

266
00:20:29,635 --> 00:20:31,205
I'm the one who messed everything up...

267
00:20:32,535 --> 00:20:33,775
because I was so foolish.

268
00:20:34,775 --> 00:20:37,705
I guess people need someone
to pour their heart into.

269
00:20:39,045 --> 00:20:40,915
For me, that person was you.

270
00:20:42,075 --> 00:20:44,585
But that's not the case anymore,
so don't feel burdened.

271
00:20:47,555 --> 00:20:48,955
Are you going to keep pushing me away?

272
00:20:52,455 --> 00:20:54,725
I understand if you're disappointed in me,
if you've lost all feelings for me.

273
00:20:55,155 --> 00:20:56,195
I would be too.

274
00:20:58,665 --> 00:21:00,635
I just didn't realize
how I felt soon enough.

275
00:21:01,895 --> 00:21:02,965
Please understand.

276
00:21:13,345 --> 00:21:14,545
Could you even accept...

277
00:21:16,685 --> 00:21:18,015
my child?

278
00:21:30,965 --> 00:21:32,795
I won't ask about the circumstances.

279
00:21:34,635 --> 00:21:35,665
Of course.

280
00:21:36,335 --> 00:21:38,665
If the baby is yours,
then they're precious and dear to me too.

281
00:21:42,675 --> 00:21:43,675
I really mean it.

282
00:21:45,905 --> 00:21:47,315
You're here in front of me right now.

283
00:21:50,545 --> 00:21:51,915
And you're looking at me.

284
00:21:52,785 --> 00:21:53,855
That's all that matters.

285
00:21:56,825 --> 00:21:58,825
I never thought
I'd have this moment again.

286
00:22:02,655 --> 00:22:04,125
That phrase, "aching with longing"...

287
00:22:04,995 --> 00:22:06,625
I thought it was just
a line in a pop song.

288
00:22:07,935 --> 00:22:09,365
But that's exactly how I felt.

289
00:22:13,035 --> 00:22:14,075
It was torture.

290
00:22:15,135 --> 00:22:16,475
I feel bad for Momo, but...

291
00:22:24,985 --> 00:22:25,985
Thank you.

292
00:22:29,255 --> 00:22:30,725
I was so pathetic...

293
00:22:31,785 --> 00:22:33,055
and completely clueless.

294
00:22:34,255 --> 00:22:36,055
It's not that you were clueless.

295
00:22:37,295 --> 00:22:39,295
It's just that Momo completely occupied...

296
00:22:39,865 --> 00:22:41,365
your heart.

297
00:22:42,395 --> 00:22:45,265
You know that saying, "Blinded by greed."

298
00:22:46,435 --> 00:22:47,635
It wasn't love.

299
00:22:48,705 --> 00:22:50,205
I just got swept away for a moment...

300
00:22:52,075 --> 00:22:53,415
by the actress, Momo.

301
00:22:57,045 --> 00:22:58,585
I know I've sinned against both of you,

302
00:23:00,045 --> 00:23:01,055
but please look kindly on me.

303
00:23:01,915 --> 00:23:03,555
I'm asking just this once.

304
00:23:07,495 --> 00:23:08,495
Now,

305
00:23:08,925 --> 00:23:10,995
I think I'm starting to get
a faint idea of what love is...

306
00:23:11,795 --> 00:23:13,325
and what it's supposed to be.

307
00:23:15,865 --> 00:23:17,265
But people say love changes.

308
00:23:17,835 --> 00:23:19,965
Love is different from a simple feeling.

309
00:23:20,105 --> 00:23:21,835
Feelings are what come and go.

310
00:23:25,945 --> 00:23:28,045
I finally get just how hard and painful
it must have been for you,

311
00:23:30,615 --> 00:23:32,215
now that I'm experiencing it myself.

312
00:23:41,995 --> 00:23:44,165
Let's just say we both messed up
because we were immature,

313
00:23:46,695 --> 00:23:48,095
and let's start over.

314
00:23:49,335 --> 00:23:51,305
The right way, for real this time.

315
00:23:58,245 --> 00:24:00,105
Things with Momo will be over
in a few months.

316
00:24:02,045 --> 00:24:03,075
I promised.

317
00:24:07,255 --> 00:24:08,655
When did you have the baby?

318
00:24:09,355 --> 00:24:11,485
Where is the baby now?
Who's taking care of it?

319
00:24:15,755 --> 00:24:18,365
You can tell me when you want to.
When you're ready.

320
00:24:18,625 --> 00:24:21,335
- What's important is...
- Remember what I say now.

321
00:24:24,765 --> 00:24:26,135
I don't regret...

322
00:24:27,405 --> 00:24:28,635
loving you.

323
00:24:29,135 --> 00:24:30,445
I have never once regretted it.

324
00:24:31,545 --> 00:24:34,445
The truth is,
I loved you more than words can say.

325
00:24:38,715 --> 00:24:39,785
And now?

326
00:24:45,225 --> 00:24:46,225
Thank you.

327
00:24:48,725 --> 00:24:49,895
Remember what I'm about
to say to you now too.

328
00:24:52,395 --> 00:24:55,035
Ha Yong Joong will never
leave Geum Ba Ra again.

329
00:24:59,535 --> 00:25:00,935
And I'll make sure of it.

330
00:25:02,605 --> 00:25:04,045
Let's watch our hair turn gray...

331
00:25:04,845 --> 00:25:06,845
and see each other grow old.

332
00:25:08,345 --> 00:25:10,585
Let's live a long, long life together.

333
00:26:16,375 --> 00:26:19,545
Do you really think you can be happy,
Ha Yong Joong, after making me cry?

334
00:26:20,215 --> 00:26:22,355
I'm going to make your life
a living torment.

335
00:26:23,215 --> 00:26:26,125
I'm not the Kim Jin Ju who was impressed
by your 100-dollar taxi fare anymore.

336
00:26:35,735 --> 00:26:36,735
Can I help you?

337
00:26:40,705 --> 00:26:41,735
The card...

338
00:26:42,375 --> 00:26:43,945
I'm just here for a delivery.

339
00:26:44,805 --> 00:26:45,805
Which unit?

340
00:26:46,545 --> 00:26:48,075
Unit 701, for Momo.

341
00:26:48,245 --> 00:26:51,485
You can't just leave it here.
Take it up to her front door.

342
00:26:51,885 --> 00:26:53,485
Her helper already went home for the day.

343
00:26:55,315 --> 00:26:57,025
Then buzz me in.

344
00:27:46,465 --> 00:27:47,535
Drive.

345
00:27:47,935 --> 00:27:49,505
- You scream, and you'll regret it!
- Dad!

346
00:27:50,645 --> 00:27:52,475
It's me, Jin Ju.

347
00:27:54,675 --> 00:27:57,345
I'm Momo now! We swapped brains!

348
00:27:58,915 --> 00:28:00,315
Don't give me that crap.

349
00:28:01,255 --> 00:28:03,615
If you don't believe me,
the surgery scar is on my head.

350
00:28:11,195 --> 00:28:12,195
Where is it?

351
00:28:23,335 --> 00:28:24,345
Proof.

352
00:28:25,075 --> 00:28:27,075
The surgery scar is the proof, Dad.

353
00:28:27,845 --> 00:28:28,915
Front door code...

354
00:28:29,515 --> 00:28:30,615
to your house.

355
00:28:32,015 --> 00:28:33,385
Which one? Hyeonmi Villa?

356
00:28:35,485 --> 00:28:36,615
What was the code again?

357
00:28:37,385 --> 00:28:38,555
It's 3-5-4-4!

358
00:28:39,885 --> 00:28:41,525
Kim Jin Ju's bank account balance.

359
00:28:42,225 --> 00:28:43,925
It was probably 10,500 dollars.

360
00:28:43,925 --> 00:28:44,995
Bank...

361
00:28:45,495 --> 00:28:47,665
- account number.
- Shinjun Bank.

362
00:28:47,935 --> 00:28:51,565
It's 222-812058-03014.

363
00:28:56,175 --> 00:28:58,045
- Drive.
- Where to?

364
00:28:58,345 --> 00:29:00,645
Home. Hyeonmi Villa.

365
00:29:04,915 --> 00:29:07,615
Don't try anything funny.
I've got nothing to lose.

366
00:29:10,285 --> 00:29:11,455
I won't, Dad.

367
00:29:13,125 --> 00:29:14,155
The Han River Park.

368
00:29:15,125 --> 00:29:16,155
Not home?

369
00:29:23,035 --> 00:29:25,935
So only your brain is Jin Ju's?

370
00:29:27,175 --> 00:29:28,175
Yes.

371
00:29:29,035 --> 00:29:30,205
Then what about the body?

372
00:29:31,345 --> 00:29:33,045
What happened to Jin Ju's body?

373
00:29:33,705 --> 00:29:34,715
I don't know.

374
00:29:35,815 --> 00:29:37,445
I can't drive, Dad.

375
00:29:37,715 --> 00:29:38,885
It's a long story.

376
00:29:40,245 --> 00:29:41,855
Can you put that away?

377
00:29:42,615 --> 00:29:43,655
I'm shaking too much.

378
00:29:53,565 --> 00:29:54,795
Is that even possible?

379
00:29:55,995 --> 00:29:57,805
It is, that's why I'm here just fine...

380
00:30:03,375 --> 00:30:04,675
How did you know, Dad?

381
00:30:04,875 --> 00:30:06,045
The earring.

382
00:30:07,675 --> 00:30:08,715
My earring?

383
00:30:08,715 --> 00:30:10,175
The one with the pearl.

384
00:30:11,885 --> 00:30:13,545
How could I forget?
Your mother bought it for you.

385
00:30:14,285 --> 00:30:16,115
It was the first gift I ever gave a woman.

386
00:30:16,885 --> 00:30:18,155
I saw it a few days ago
at Director Shin's hospital...

387
00:30:18,155 --> 00:30:19,785
when you took photos with your fans.

388
00:30:20,285 --> 00:30:21,725
Dad, you were there?

389
00:30:22,055 --> 00:30:23,055
So...

390
00:30:25,225 --> 00:30:26,295
your body...

391
00:30:27,365 --> 00:30:28,865
is just gone?

392
00:30:34,475 --> 00:30:35,535
How could...

393
00:30:36,905 --> 00:30:38,105
That bastard Director Shin.

394
00:30:38,405 --> 00:30:40,175
Director Shin isn't at fault here.

395
00:30:40,175 --> 00:30:42,345
There are certain lines you don't cross.

396
00:30:46,085 --> 00:30:47,515
Did you ask for this,

397
00:30:47,955 --> 00:30:49,055
or were you offered it?

398
00:30:52,155 --> 00:30:54,155
- You wretched girl!
- Dad!

399
00:30:54,155 --> 00:30:55,755
Don't you call me Dad.

400
00:30:57,865 --> 00:30:59,295
To cut ties with your own father,

401
00:31:00,635 --> 00:31:02,535
you'd go as far as killing your own body.

402
00:31:03,065 --> 00:31:04,365
I was scared.

403
00:31:06,135 --> 00:31:07,435
Scared of your own father?

404
00:31:08,675 --> 00:31:10,075
What did I ever do to you?

405
00:31:10,135 --> 00:31:11,275
It's just...

406
00:31:12,405 --> 00:31:14,245
I was sick and tired of everything.

407
00:31:15,015 --> 00:31:16,315
It wasn't really because of you.

408
00:31:16,545 --> 00:31:17,615
Then...

409
00:31:18,445 --> 00:31:20,485
why didn't you tell me after the surgery?

410
00:31:22,385 --> 00:31:24,725
If the world found out, I'd be finished.

411
00:31:25,285 --> 00:31:27,225
I was going to come find you
once things blew over.

412
00:31:28,225 --> 00:31:29,225
I swear.

413
00:31:32,895 --> 00:31:35,665
And living as Momo hasn't been easy.

414
00:31:35,735 --> 00:31:37,435
Why are you and Ha Yong Joong separated?

415
00:31:40,405 --> 00:31:42,935
- We just drifted apart.
- Who did?

416
00:31:43,735 --> 00:31:46,045
- Both of us.
- You sure he didn't figure it out?

417
00:31:46,175 --> 00:31:47,945
It's more complicated than that.

418
00:31:48,215 --> 00:31:50,015
It was just a lot of things piling up.

419
00:31:57,185 --> 00:31:58,225
Wire me some money.

420
00:31:59,225 --> 00:32:00,255
Send one big one for now.

421
00:32:00,725 --> 00:32:01,755
A thousand dollars?

422
00:32:02,825 --> 00:32:03,925
Ten thousand dollars?

423
00:32:05,425 --> 00:32:07,735
Is a big one, only 10,000 dollars
for someone like Momo?

424
00:32:09,595 --> 00:32:12,205
The daily limit is 50,000 dollars.

425
00:32:13,105 --> 00:32:15,275
Then send
the other 50,000 dollars tomorrow.

426
00:32:15,275 --> 00:32:17,305
Then wire 200,000 dollars by the weekend.

427
00:32:17,505 --> 00:32:18,975
Go to the bank in person if you have to.

428
00:32:24,885 --> 00:32:27,015
After severing family ties like that,

429
00:32:27,555 --> 00:32:29,055
did you really think you could be happy?

430
00:32:29,685 --> 00:32:30,855
The sky...

431
00:32:31,985 --> 00:32:33,225
will punish you.

432
00:32:36,095 --> 00:32:37,095
Woosung Bank.

433
00:32:38,025 --> 00:32:39,125
Account 5-2-5...

434
00:32:41,795 --> 00:32:43,235
I don't have any beer.

435
00:32:43,235 --> 00:32:44,305
Will a Coke do?

436
00:32:44,365 --> 00:32:45,565
Then...

437
00:32:47,475 --> 00:32:48,505
Liquor.

438
00:32:49,035 --> 00:32:50,235
Whiskey.

439
00:32:50,905 --> 00:32:52,045
Give me the key card too.

440
00:33:19,305 --> 00:33:21,875
Aren't you hot?
Why are you still wearing that?

441
00:33:22,375 --> 00:33:23,605
I have a bit of a cold.

442
00:33:23,735 --> 00:33:25,705
The code to Director Shin's penthouse.

443
00:33:28,375 --> 00:33:31,885
- Why?
- So I know. Stop asking questions.

444
00:33:49,335 --> 00:33:50,635
After you two break up,

445
00:33:51,805 --> 00:33:53,305
should I ask Director Shin...

446
00:33:54,135 --> 00:33:56,305
to turn me into Ha Yong Joong?

447
00:33:59,905 --> 00:34:01,075
How much does it hurt?

448
00:34:04,485 --> 00:34:06,285
You can't go through that twice, Dad.

449
00:34:09,055 --> 00:34:10,055
Is that...

450
00:34:10,055 --> 00:34:11,225
Sonbeni?

451
00:35:06,545 --> 00:35:08,215
(Nua General Hospital)

452
00:35:12,115 --> 00:35:13,185
Are you nervous?

453
00:35:15,255 --> 00:35:16,285
Don't worry.

454
00:35:19,485 --> 00:35:20,995
I might treat you coldly.

455
00:35:22,125 --> 00:35:23,725
But you'll have Momo's face.

456
00:35:39,175 --> 00:35:40,405
Just relax.

457
00:35:41,215 --> 00:35:42,245
And try to get some sleep.

458
00:37:52,205 --> 00:37:53,205
Oh my gosh!

459
00:37:54,145 --> 00:37:56,915
- How did you get in here?
- What do you mean?

460
00:37:57,275 --> 00:37:59,345
You gave me the key card.

461
00:38:00,045 --> 00:38:01,055
Who did?

462
00:38:01,455 --> 00:38:02,555
Playing dumb again?

463
00:38:02,885 --> 00:38:03,885
It's just...

464
00:38:06,025 --> 00:38:07,155
By any chance,

465
00:38:07,855 --> 00:38:09,455
did you get it from Jin Ju?

466
00:38:10,625 --> 00:38:12,125
You changed the passcode, didn't you?

467
00:38:13,065 --> 00:38:14,125
Open up.

468
00:38:14,865 --> 00:38:16,395
Should I just spill everything?

469
00:38:16,395 --> 00:38:18,365
A strange man keeps ringing my doorbell.

470
00:38:18,435 --> 00:38:21,005
Please come quickly.
Noir Hospital, 21st floor.

471
00:38:21,905 --> 00:38:22,905
Yes.

472
00:38:42,155 --> 00:38:43,255
What about Ba Ra?

473
00:38:55,605 --> 00:38:56,735
Ma'am!

474
00:39:17,895 --> 00:39:19,025
It's Mommy.

475
00:39:19,995 --> 00:39:21,095
Remember me, okay?

476
00:39:23,465 --> 00:39:25,235
I'll come back safe and sound...

477
00:39:25,765 --> 00:39:27,705
and give my baby boy many hugs.

478
00:39:28,835 --> 00:39:30,235
Eat well,

479
00:39:31,205 --> 00:39:32,545
and sleep well.

480
00:39:45,325 --> 00:39:46,355
I love you.

481
00:39:48,695 --> 00:39:50,425
I love you, my sweet baby.

482
00:40:39,275 --> 00:40:40,705
(New Message, Actress Momo)

483
00:40:40,705 --> 00:40:42,545
Reporter Geum Ba Ra,
is this a good time to talk?

484
00:40:46,985 --> 00:40:48,455
(Actress Momo)

485
00:40:52,085 --> 00:40:54,455
Hello, Ms. Geum.

486
00:40:54,825 --> 00:40:56,125
Momo.

487
00:40:56,495 --> 00:40:59,895
I'm at my villa having some wine.

488
00:41:01,435 --> 00:41:02,765
With friends?

489
00:41:03,295 --> 00:41:05,465
No, I'm alone.

490
00:41:06,735 --> 00:41:08,835
And I found myself thinking of you.

491
00:41:09,375 --> 00:41:11,105
The look in your eyes, to be exact.

492
00:41:12,505 --> 00:41:14,205
Was the look in my eyes...

493
00:41:15,145 --> 00:41:16,415
bad?

494
00:41:16,875 --> 00:41:18,315
I'll tell you when you get here.

495
00:41:20,445 --> 00:41:21,655
Where is your villa?

496
00:41:22,085 --> 00:41:24,985
If you text me your address,
I'll send my manager.

497
00:41:25,055 --> 00:41:26,085
He'll give you a ride here.

498
00:41:26,725 --> 00:41:28,195
The buses don't come out this far.

499
00:42:08,035 --> 00:42:09,035
Goodness.

500
00:42:10,335 --> 00:42:11,335
Go ahead, take it.

501
00:42:14,335 --> 00:42:17,475
Director, if it's not urgent,
can I call you back?

502
00:42:17,835 --> 00:42:18,845
Okay.

503
00:42:19,905 --> 00:42:22,015
I'm sorry you have to see me like this.

504
00:42:23,775 --> 00:42:25,045
Is something wrong?

505
00:42:25,745 --> 00:42:28,615
No, I really was just thinking of you.

506
00:42:29,315 --> 00:42:31,425
And I'm sorry to bother you
on your day off.

507
00:42:31,485 --> 00:42:35,155
Are you kidding?
An invitation from you is an honor.

508
00:42:35,225 --> 00:42:37,225
Since we met at that
Japanese restaurant by chance,

509
00:42:37,225 --> 00:42:40,025
I think about the look in your eyes.

510
00:42:40,595 --> 00:42:42,995
It was so indifferent, I guess?

511
00:42:45,335 --> 00:42:47,505
You didn't see me as Momo the actress.

512
00:42:47,505 --> 00:42:49,635
You saw me as a regular person.

513
00:42:50,705 --> 00:42:52,745
I figured you'd be uncomfortable
if I made a big deal out of it.

514
00:42:53,175 --> 00:42:54,275
Exactly.

515
00:42:55,375 --> 00:42:59,515
To put it a bit dramatically,

516
00:43:00,085 --> 00:43:02,485
unlike how people's eyes pounce on me,

517
00:43:03,055 --> 00:43:04,785
you were a breath of fresh air.

518
00:43:05,825 --> 00:43:07,825
You made me feel at ease, and I liked it.

519
00:43:08,125 --> 00:43:10,725
That's a relief.
I'm glad you took it that way.

520
00:43:10,955 --> 00:43:13,525
You were putting yourself in my shoes,
weren't you?

521
00:43:14,865 --> 00:43:16,665
I know what it's like for actors.

522
00:43:16,995 --> 00:43:18,935
You're constantly hounded by people.

523
00:43:20,765 --> 00:43:22,235
I'm sure it's something
to be grateful for.

524
00:43:22,535 --> 00:43:24,705
A lot of times, it can be overwhelming.

525
00:43:30,215 --> 00:43:31,785
Could you be like a big sister to me?

526
00:43:32,245 --> 00:43:34,015
Treat me like your little sister.

527
00:43:36,415 --> 00:43:37,655
Do you have any younger siblings?

528
00:43:38,955 --> 00:43:40,185
I'm an only child, too.

529
00:43:40,725 --> 00:43:43,695
Weren't you ever jealous of friends
who had older siblings?

530
00:43:45,195 --> 00:43:47,465
But at least you have your parents, Momo.

531
00:43:48,035 --> 00:43:49,795
I grew up in an orphanage.

532
00:43:50,395 --> 00:43:52,905
Goodness, I had no idea.

533
00:43:54,835 --> 00:43:58,945
I'm used to people being taken aback
with that expression.

534
00:43:59,775 --> 00:44:03,975
I'm not taken aback.
I assumed you grew up with a silver spoon.

535
00:44:04,145 --> 00:44:05,585
You just give off that vibe.

536
00:44:07,115 --> 00:44:08,155
I do?

537
00:44:08,855 --> 00:44:11,585
That makes you even more amazing.
That sobered me right up.

538
00:44:15,295 --> 00:44:18,995
I was going to vent,
but I'd rather hear your story instead.

539
00:44:19,225 --> 00:44:21,165
I'm not just being nosy.

540
00:44:21,295 --> 00:44:22,565
There's not much to tell.

541
00:44:23,265 --> 00:44:27,035
Orphanages these days are a lot nicer
than you'd think.

542
00:44:43,555 --> 00:44:45,325
Oh, you made gimbap?

543
00:44:45,555 --> 00:44:48,395
I was in the middle of making some
when you called.

544
00:44:49,055 --> 00:44:51,595
But we don't have any fruit.
I should've bought some.

545
00:44:51,595 --> 00:44:52,925
That's okay. We don't need any.

546
00:44:53,295 --> 00:44:54,495
I have plenty of snacks instead.

547
00:45:05,175 --> 00:45:06,645
Gosh, this is amazing.

548
00:45:06,705 --> 00:45:09,015
I've never had gimbap like this before.

549
00:45:09,645 --> 00:45:10,975
It's aged kimchi gimbap.

550
00:45:11,485 --> 00:45:13,545
I just threw it together with what I had.

551
00:45:14,045 --> 00:45:16,285
Aged kimchi makes it taste so...

552
00:45:16,685 --> 00:45:18,655
It's so clean, yet so flavorful.

553
00:45:20,025 --> 00:45:21,255
You probably shouldn't gain weight.

554
00:45:21,255 --> 00:45:22,695
I'll just starve myself tomorrow.

555
00:45:23,425 --> 00:45:24,965
Fasting is just part of the job.

556
00:45:30,535 --> 00:45:31,965
It must be stressful, right?

557
00:45:32,965 --> 00:45:36,305
From what I see,
actors lose just as much as they gain.

558
00:45:36,575 --> 00:45:39,875
That reporter, Lee Si Kyung,
is out for my blood.

559
00:45:40,175 --> 00:45:41,715
Does he really hate me that much?

560
00:45:42,445 --> 00:45:44,945
- You saw the articles, right?
- Think of him as your nemesis.

561
00:45:45,085 --> 00:45:46,645
We all have one.

562
00:45:48,015 --> 00:45:49,985
For me, the world itself was my nemesis.

563
00:45:50,485 --> 00:45:52,625
I must sound pathetic,
whining in front of you.

564
00:45:52,685 --> 00:45:55,155
I'm not judging.
If anything, I understand you better.

565
00:45:55,255 --> 00:45:59,395
There's this very popular veteran actress.
We were in a show together.

566
00:45:59,995 --> 00:46:03,035
She kept saying how unique and pretty
my bag was and asked me for it,

567
00:46:03,295 --> 00:46:06,235
but I told her I couldn't
since a fan made it for me.

568
00:46:07,235 --> 00:46:09,505
Since then, she's been bad-mouthing me.

569
00:46:09,635 --> 00:46:10,675
You're kidding.

570
00:46:10,675 --> 00:46:14,245
Saying I have the worst attitude
and that I don't even say hello.

571
00:46:14,675 --> 00:46:16,315
But I've never even left her on read.

572
00:46:17,975 --> 00:46:20,945
She's raising two daughters of her own.
How can she act like that?

573
00:46:21,085 --> 00:46:23,785
What if her daughters go out in the world
and someone treats them the same way?

574
00:46:25,555 --> 00:46:27,825
The world doesn't run on common sense.

575
00:46:27,825 --> 00:46:29,255
And people aren't always what you expect.

576
00:46:29,825 --> 00:46:31,095
I think...

577
00:46:31,455 --> 00:46:34,695
the world has half and half.
Half are good, and half are bad.

578
00:46:36,965 --> 00:46:39,305
Will evil people ever just disappear?

579
00:46:40,605 --> 00:46:42,235
The world has no use for them.

580
00:46:42,235 --> 00:46:43,805
They'll never go away.

581
00:46:44,845 --> 00:46:47,005
The universe has day and night, right?

582
00:46:47,405 --> 00:46:49,245
As long as the universe exists,

583
00:46:49,245 --> 00:46:52,485
the human world, just like day and night,
will have good people and bad people.

584
00:46:54,345 --> 00:46:56,185
You just have to accept it for what it is.

585
00:46:56,585 --> 00:46:59,255
As long as we're not the evil ones
hurting others,

586
00:46:59,525 --> 00:47:01,625
we can take comfort in that
and be at peace.

587
00:47:03,255 --> 00:47:04,455
Is it that easy for you?

588
00:47:06,465 --> 00:47:09,135
I've been slandered and had my share
of hard times, too.

589
00:47:09,435 --> 00:47:11,065
But at some point, it just clicked.

590
00:47:12,365 --> 00:47:13,835
They say humans mirror the universe...

591
00:47:13,835 --> 00:47:16,675
I guess it’s the same principle,
the same phenomenon...

592
00:47:17,535 --> 00:47:21,715
I realized I shouldn't get caught up in it
and just stick to my own path.

593
00:47:27,785 --> 00:47:29,085
You're so right.

594
00:47:29,655 --> 00:47:31,015
You really are something else.

595
00:47:31,085 --> 00:47:33,555
Our bodies don't just have healthy cells.

596
00:47:33,755 --> 00:47:35,755
They constantly create cancer cells, too,

597
00:47:35,825 --> 00:47:36,855
every single day.

598
00:47:38,125 --> 00:47:40,195
I really shouldn't let it get to me.

599
00:47:40,995 --> 00:47:42,895
I feel so much better already.

600
00:47:44,495 --> 00:47:47,135
Okay, from now on, you're my big sister.

601
00:47:49,505 --> 00:47:51,305
We're even wearing similar outfits today.

602
00:47:52,405 --> 00:47:54,005
Right. Only the colors are different.

603
00:47:54,145 --> 00:47:56,375
Let's trade to celebrate being sisters.

604
00:47:57,545 --> 00:47:59,785
Your shirt's silk, Momo.

605
00:48:00,285 --> 00:48:02,215
I got mine for 25 dollars
at a discount store.

606
00:48:02,385 --> 00:48:05,285
Why so formal? We can be casual now.

607
00:48:05,355 --> 00:48:08,795
I won't call you "Reporter Geum" anymore.
I'll call you Ba Ra.

608
00:49:29,475 --> 00:49:30,935
James, I've been thinking.

609
00:49:31,005 --> 00:49:32,445
Looking at how confident Ba Ra is,

610
00:49:33,245 --> 00:49:34,475
do you think she might've had my baby?

611
00:49:34,475 --> 00:49:36,675
You think I haven't thought of that?

612
00:49:37,445 --> 00:49:39,015
But no, the timeline doesn't add up.

613
00:49:39,515 --> 00:49:41,715
Park Sun Woo said she looked like
she was 6 or 7 months along.

614
00:49:41,785 --> 00:49:43,785
She probably just said that
to get you to give up.

615
00:49:44,185 --> 00:49:45,355
Then why did she just disappear?

616
00:49:45,785 --> 00:49:48,025
Because she couldn't bear to see
you and Momo together.

617
00:49:48,855 --> 00:49:50,355
How is she acting toward you?

618
00:49:51,125 --> 00:49:52,225
She's different than before.

619
00:49:52,925 --> 00:49:55,535
She's a bit cold,
and she's keeping her distance.

620
00:49:56,965 --> 00:49:58,235
It's all because I didn't listen to you...

621
00:49:58,835 --> 00:50:00,665
Do you think it's easy
to get pregnant on the first try?

622
00:50:01,305 --> 00:50:02,835
But if she really did have my baby...

623
00:50:02,975 --> 00:50:04,505
She could have had a miscarriage.

624
00:50:05,245 --> 00:50:06,675
Out of spite, couldn't she have gone...

625
00:50:06,675 --> 00:50:08,975
to one of the guys
who were fawning over her?

626
00:50:09,615 --> 00:50:11,375
Even I had a thing for Reporter Geum.

627
00:50:11,915 --> 00:50:16,315
A Sungwoo Daily reporter meets top players
in politics, finance, and culture.

628
00:50:16,555 --> 00:50:17,555
Among them...

629
00:50:18,725 --> 00:50:20,355
If she still loved you...

630
00:50:20,485 --> 00:50:23,095
or was pregnant with your baby,
she would've come to you.

631
00:50:23,295 --> 00:50:24,355
Why would she go to Director Shin?

632
00:50:25,365 --> 00:50:28,535
Don't jump to conclusions.
I'll meet with Reporter Geum and find out.

633
00:50:28,965 --> 00:50:30,965
She'll be discharged
right after her MRI, won't she?

634
00:50:31,835 --> 00:50:33,365
She's not going to disappear again,
is she?

635
00:50:34,005 --> 00:50:36,075
If she meant to, she would've gone
to another hospital in the first place.

636
00:50:47,145 --> 00:50:48,145
Mom.

637
00:50:49,255 --> 00:50:50,255
Dad.

638
00:50:51,285 --> 00:50:52,285
My little sister.

639
00:50:53,825 --> 00:50:55,895
Our family of four was all together.

640
00:51:02,195 --> 00:51:03,195
Mom.

641
00:51:10,375 --> 00:51:11,575
Goodbye,

642
00:51:12,875 --> 00:51:13,875
Geum Ba Ra.

643
00:51:35,395 --> 00:51:37,395
I miss Oiji and Pickles.

644
00:51:40,205 --> 00:51:42,305
(Artist Paul Kim)

645
00:51:46,105 --> 00:51:47,205
Mr. Kim.

646
00:51:47,205 --> 00:51:49,845
Hello. It must be late in Korea, right?

647
00:51:49,975 --> 00:51:52,845
I've still got a while before I turn in.
Are you overseas again?

648
00:51:53,415 --> 00:51:54,415
Yes.

649
00:51:55,785 --> 00:51:57,455
I got curious and searched online,

650
00:51:57,955 --> 00:52:00,325
and an article about
Momo's separation popped up.

651
00:52:00,955 --> 00:52:02,155
I was just wondering if it's true.

652
00:52:02,995 --> 00:52:04,625
I didn't feel comfortable
asking them myself.

653
00:52:05,525 --> 00:52:06,525
Yes, it's true.

654
00:52:06,895 --> 00:52:08,165
What's the issue?

655
00:52:08,635 --> 00:52:13,305
It seems they just naturally drifted apart
after her last miscarriage.

656
00:52:15,875 --> 00:52:17,105
I feel somewhat responsible.

657
00:52:17,235 --> 00:52:20,675
Why would you feel responsible?
That goes for me, too.

658
00:52:20,905 --> 00:52:23,015
They say only the couple truly knows
what goes on in a marriage.

659
00:52:24,415 --> 00:52:26,115
Let me treat you to a meal
when I get back to Korea.

660
00:52:26,415 --> 00:52:27,945
With Reporter Geum Ba Ra
from Sungwoo Daily.

661
00:52:28,785 --> 00:52:29,955
You know Reporter Geum, don't you?

662
00:52:31,285 --> 00:52:32,785
Are you close? With Reporter Geum Ba Ra?

663
00:52:33,225 --> 00:52:34,225
Yes.

664
00:52:34,585 --> 00:52:37,425
I asked her to check in on my place
every now and then before I left,

665
00:52:38,195 --> 00:52:39,325
but it turns out
she took a leave of absence.

666
00:52:41,065 --> 00:52:42,695
When was the last time you saw her?

667
00:52:51,175 --> 00:52:52,545
I have no choice.

668
00:52:53,905 --> 00:52:55,315
My little sister, Momo,

669
00:52:55,975 --> 00:52:59,015
was a truly good soul who despised evil.

670
00:53:00,415 --> 00:53:02,015
But into her angelic body...

671
00:53:02,815 --> 00:53:04,515
went the brain of Kim Jin Ju.

672
00:53:05,785 --> 00:53:08,385
Can you imagine how horrifying
and agonizing it must be for her soul?

673
00:53:10,095 --> 00:53:11,755
I will give up my own body.

674
00:53:12,825 --> 00:53:13,825
To me...

675
00:53:14,965 --> 00:53:16,795
my sister is more important.

676
00:53:51,565 --> 00:53:53,205
Reporter Geum wasn't pregnant.

677
00:53:53,335 --> 00:53:54,935
Either that, or Park Sun Woo was wrong.

678
00:53:56,275 --> 00:53:58,035
I just got off the phone with Paul Kim,

679
00:53:58,535 --> 00:54:01,075
and he said Ba Ra was house-sitting
for him in Yangpyeong.

680
00:54:34,175 --> 00:54:35,545
She also looked
after a colleague's grandmother...

681
00:54:35,545 --> 00:54:36,715
who was stationed overseas.

682
00:54:36,975 --> 00:54:39,245
Paul Kim could've been mistaken, you know.

683
00:54:39,315 --> 00:54:43,215
If you were talking to her face-to-face,
couldn't you tell if she's pregnant?

684
00:54:43,515 --> 00:54:44,815
Maybe not in the early stages, sure.

685
00:54:47,085 --> 00:54:49,955
She was probably upset and said that
just to get under your skin.

686
00:54:51,495 --> 00:54:54,065
If her MRI comes back clear,
she'll probably go straight to Yangpyeong.

687
00:54:54,525 --> 00:54:56,595
You have to stop her, get on your knees,
do whatever it takes.

688
00:54:57,765 --> 00:55:01,105
It's also possible she showed up
since your separation article gave hope.

689
00:55:05,475 --> 00:55:07,545
My imagination was running wild too.

690
00:55:08,645 --> 00:55:09,975
Anyway, what a relief.

691
00:55:23,995 --> 00:55:26,265
(Nua General Hospital)

692
00:55:54,325 --> 00:55:55,655
Has Geum Ba Ra been discharged?

693
00:55:56,625 --> 00:55:58,655
She's one of the Director's patients,
so we wouldn't know.

694
00:56:01,725 --> 00:56:03,635
He isn't seeing patients today.

695
00:56:03,635 --> 00:56:05,535
He might be at a conference.

696
00:56:07,665 --> 00:56:10,935
The Director said Geum Ba Ra had an MRI.
Did she have it done?

697
00:56:11,175 --> 00:56:12,675
We have no way of knowing.

698
00:56:13,245 --> 00:56:14,305
Why not?

699
00:56:15,105 --> 00:56:16,245
There's no record of it.

700
00:56:27,225 --> 00:56:30,025
The phone you are calling is turned off.
Please leave a message...

701
00:56:30,025 --> 00:56:31,555
(Ju Shin)

702
00:56:35,995 --> 00:56:37,495
(Ba Ra)

703
00:56:40,235 --> 00:56:43,235
The phone you are calling is turned off.
Please leave a message after the tone.

704
00:56:43,875 --> 00:56:44,875
(Ba Ra)

705
00:56:47,075 --> 00:56:48,145
What's with both of them?

706
00:57:38,525 --> 00:57:39,525
Welcome, sir.

707
00:57:41,195 --> 00:57:42,995
Is this the one? The new model?

708
00:57:43,135 --> 00:57:44,195
Yes, it is.

709
00:57:46,205 --> 00:57:47,535
Can I get you something to drink?

710
00:57:47,905 --> 00:57:50,305
- An iced Americano.
- An iced Americano?

711
00:57:50,805 --> 00:57:51,805
Yes.

712
00:57:53,105 --> 00:57:55,575
- If I order one, how long is the wait?
- It's a three-month wait.

713
00:57:55,715 --> 00:57:56,715
Really? That long?

714
00:57:59,385 --> 00:58:00,745
Is there any way to get it sooner?

715
01:00:44,045 --> 01:00:45,885
I need Paul Kim's Yangpyeong address.

716
01:00:46,015 --> 01:00:47,015
You're going there?

717
01:00:47,185 --> 01:00:49,555
- Yes.
- It's no use. We were...

718
01:00:50,785 --> 01:00:52,085
You're a step too late.

719
01:00:52,855 --> 01:00:55,025
Has Director Shin ever
turned his phone off and gone MIA?

720
01:00:57,025 --> 01:00:59,825
The whole MRI thing
could've just been a ploy.

721
01:01:00,365 --> 01:01:01,925
Just to keep her at the hospital.

722
01:01:03,565 --> 01:01:05,065
Looks like the two of them
left the country.

723
01:01:09,905 --> 01:01:12,575
I really don't think
you two are meant to be.

724
01:01:13,345 --> 01:01:14,345
Just let her go.

725
01:01:15,775 --> 01:01:18,075
(Momo)

726
01:01:20,445 --> 01:01:22,245
The phone you are calling is turned off.

727
01:01:22,245 --> 01:01:24,655
Please leave your message after the tone.

728
01:01:25,455 --> 01:01:29,095
That brat. Her father has stomach cancer.

729
01:01:32,925 --> 01:01:34,695
- Samhap.
- You brought takeout?

730
01:01:34,695 --> 01:01:37,235
Yes, from the manager's favorite spot
in Mokpo.

731
01:01:37,565 --> 01:01:39,665
- I can't eat this.
- Me neither.

732
01:01:39,735 --> 01:01:40,735
Then why did you get it?

733
01:01:41,705 --> 01:01:43,535
I can barely breathe just from the smell.

734
01:01:44,035 --> 01:01:45,305
It's a miracle cure for constipation.

735
01:01:45,305 --> 01:01:47,005
My mom swears by it.

736
01:01:47,505 --> 01:01:49,915
- But still...
- I'm serious.

737
01:01:50,475 --> 01:01:52,615
This is to help with your constipation.

738
01:01:54,945 --> 01:01:56,185
And I'll eat it with you.

739
01:02:03,255 --> 01:02:05,895
- What about your mom?
- My mom has plans most nights.

740
01:02:14,735 --> 01:02:15,735
Just pinch your nose.

741
01:02:18,375 --> 01:02:19,375
Go on, eat up.

742
01:02:19,705 --> 01:02:20,705
Together.

743
01:02:53,505 --> 01:02:55,445
How can this even be considered food?

744
01:02:55,815 --> 01:02:58,245
We probably need to eat seven pieces
for it to work, right?

745
01:02:59,885 --> 01:03:01,445
Even I'm eating it,
and I'm not even constipated.

746
01:03:04,685 --> 01:03:06,285
You're not just doing this to be nice.

747
01:03:06,685 --> 01:03:09,055
I haven't done anything to deserve this,
have I, Momo?

748
01:03:10,955 --> 01:03:14,365
My mom says it also clears up your skin.

749
01:03:14,525 --> 01:03:15,665
My skin is clear.

750
01:03:16,235 --> 01:03:17,865
Just close your eyes and do it.

751
01:03:18,265 --> 01:03:19,965
I'm going to eat seven pieces
right along with you.

752
01:03:23,105 --> 01:03:24,375
Alright, fine.
Since you went to all this trouble.

753
01:03:25,035 --> 01:03:26,045
Exactly.

754
01:03:39,185 --> 01:03:40,185
I, too,

755
01:03:40,655 --> 01:03:42,655
can do anything for my little sister.

756
01:04:16,125 --> 01:04:17,125
You did great.

757
01:04:18,895 --> 01:04:20,695
Jin Ju...

758
01:04:22,325 --> 01:04:23,335
Not yet.

759
01:04:44,755 --> 01:04:47,085
She really needs to be taught a lesson.
She really does.

760
01:04:47,825 --> 01:04:49,855
She must have seen my missed calls.

761
01:05:02,675 --> 01:05:03,675
What?

762
01:05:04,935 --> 01:05:06,175
Was Ba Ra discharged?

763
01:05:07,475 --> 01:05:09,545
- No.
- Then what?

764
01:05:10,515 --> 01:05:11,715
She had a brain hemorrhage.

765
01:05:13,085 --> 01:05:14,085
A brain hemorrhage?

766
01:05:16,985 --> 01:05:17,985
And?

767
01:05:19,455 --> 01:05:21,555
- We did emergency surgery.
- You did it yourself?

768
01:05:22,895 --> 01:05:25,025
- When?
- The day before yesterday.

769
01:05:25,355 --> 01:05:26,665
Then why didn't you tell me?

770
01:05:27,225 --> 01:05:28,225
How is she?

771
01:05:30,065 --> 01:05:32,165
- How is she?
- It's only been a day.

772
01:05:33,335 --> 01:05:34,405
She's in the recovery room now.

773
01:05:36,635 --> 01:05:38,105
Then why don't the nurses know anything?

774
01:05:38,235 --> 01:05:39,345
It's what Ba Ra wanted.

775
01:05:41,045 --> 01:05:42,375
She doesn't want people to know.

776
01:05:43,275 --> 01:05:44,675
You even had your phone off.

777
01:05:45,775 --> 01:05:46,785
How was I...

778
01:05:48,415 --> 01:05:49,915
supposed to know
I'd be operating on Ba Ra?

779
01:05:56,955 --> 01:05:58,955
(Ready for surgery)

780
01:05:59,055 --> 01:06:00,065
I have to go into surgery.

781
01:06:02,765 --> 01:06:04,035
Let me see her, just for a second.

782
01:06:19,545 --> 01:06:20,545
Ba Ra.

783
01:06:21,385 --> 01:06:24,685
Were you in so much pain that
a vessel in your brain burst?

784
01:06:26,125 --> 01:06:28,155
Please recover without any complications.

785
01:06:29,025 --> 01:06:30,825
I'm going to stay by your side forever.

786
01:06:39,705 --> 01:06:40,705
Kim...

787
01:06:44,075 --> 01:06:45,335
Jin Ju.

788
01:06:52,745 --> 01:06:54,085
Is there anyone at all we can call?

789
01:06:58,215 --> 01:06:59,355
I'll try.

790
01:07:00,325 --> 01:07:02,855
Wait, you can't do the surgery
without a guardian's consent?

791
01:07:09,225 --> 01:07:11,165
The phone you are calling is turned off.

792
01:07:11,235 --> 01:07:12,965
Please leave a message after the tone.

793
01:07:13,505 --> 01:07:14,735
It's off.

794
01:07:15,465 --> 01:07:16,605
You know...

795
01:07:17,305 --> 01:07:19,035
The director here should know her.

796
01:07:19,875 --> 01:07:22,975
Her name's Geum Ba Ra.
She's a reporter for the Sungwoo Daily.

797
01:07:23,415 --> 01:07:26,315
He says he'll ask Geum Ba Ra
to sign the surgical consent form.

798
01:07:26,585 --> 01:07:27,585
And it hasn't metastasized?

799
01:07:28,015 --> 01:07:29,015
That's right.

800
01:07:30,285 --> 01:07:33,355
- His registration number.
- It's 6663256.

801
01:07:33,525 --> 01:07:35,355
The phone you are calling is turned off...

802
01:07:36,555 --> 01:07:37,895
That brat...

803
01:07:38,455 --> 01:07:40,195
Her father has stomach cancer.

804
01:07:41,265 --> 01:07:43,795
Don't tell me she ran off again.

805
01:07:44,765 --> 01:07:48,465
Even if she did, her face is famous.
How hard can it be to find her?

806
01:07:55,745 --> 01:07:57,445
What kind of patients
do you usually look after?

807
01:07:58,745 --> 01:08:00,315
Post-op patients, mostly.

808
01:08:00,315 --> 01:08:02,645
For stage one,
you have nothing to worry about.

809
01:08:04,555 --> 01:08:06,655
When can I eat after the surgery?

810
01:08:18,035 --> 01:08:20,835
(Move her tomorrow morning.)

811
01:08:31,145 --> 01:08:32,175
Watch this when you're ready.

812
01:08:57,375 --> 01:08:58,375
Momo.

813
01:08:59,545 --> 01:09:00,675
Will this work now?

814
01:09:01,975 --> 01:09:03,015
Will it?

815
01:09:50,955 --> 01:09:52,355
(Patient transport only)

816
01:09:54,695 --> 01:09:55,995
(Counseling for epilepsy patients
and their families)

817
01:10:29,525 --> 01:10:32,065
When can we see her? She must be awake.

818
01:10:32,165 --> 01:10:33,205
It was brain surgery,

819
01:10:33,465 --> 01:10:34,705
so not until she's moved
to a general ward.

820
01:10:35,005 --> 01:10:37,675
This is unbelievable.
I mean, at her age, how could this...

821
01:10:38,275 --> 01:10:39,805
It's not like she drank or smoked.

822
01:10:41,175 --> 01:10:43,345
Could her vessels be weak from poor eating
when she was at the orphanage?

823
01:10:44,875 --> 01:10:45,875
Mr. Kim Gwang Cheol.

824
01:10:47,045 --> 01:10:48,085
Try to open your eyes.

825
01:10:49,885 --> 01:10:51,685
Just you try running off again.

826
01:10:53,055 --> 01:10:54,825
I'll find you if you do.

827
01:10:55,485 --> 01:10:56,525
Mr. Kim Gwang Cheol?

828
01:10:59,195 --> 01:11:01,125
Your surgery went well.

829
01:11:30,655 --> 01:11:31,655
Did she...

830
01:11:32,455 --> 01:11:33,925
go on a trip or something?

831
01:12:07,325 --> 01:12:09,425
(Cashier's check)

832
01:12:18,135 --> 01:12:20,745
To be honest,
you're the one I find most intimidating.

833
01:12:20,875 --> 01:12:23,245
Well, don't be.
You can be comfortable with me.

834
01:12:26,445 --> 01:12:28,115
It's not that I don't trust you,
Director Shin.

835
01:12:37,225 --> 01:12:38,425
Move her to the 12th floor.

836
01:12:38,695 --> 01:12:39,695
Yes, sir.

837
01:12:48,335 --> 01:12:50,235
- Nua General Hospital.
- Yes, sir.

838
01:12:53,375 --> 01:12:54,645
(Neurosurgery Director's Office)

839
01:12:54,845 --> 01:12:55,845
How's Ba Ra?

840
01:13:02,815 --> 01:13:03,815
Brain-dead?

841
01:13:09,485 --> 01:13:10,495
How could this...

842
01:13:12,225 --> 01:13:13,495
You're the one who operated.

843
01:13:18,265 --> 01:13:19,265
What now?

844
01:13:22,005 --> 01:13:24,405
- There's nothing I can do.
- What do you mean, nothing?

845
01:13:25,905 --> 01:13:28,305
You have to find a way, whatever it takes.

846
01:13:30,145 --> 01:13:31,145
Shin Ju Shin.

847
01:13:32,875 --> 01:13:35,085
You have to make her wake up.

848
01:13:38,555 --> 01:13:39,555
You think I haven't tried everything?

849
01:13:40,485 --> 01:13:41,485
Then, operate again.

850
01:13:44,255 --> 01:13:45,255
You crazy bastard.

851
01:13:46,095 --> 01:13:47,225
After everything, you did this to Ba Ra...

852
01:13:48,195 --> 01:13:49,195
This is it?

853
01:13:54,305 --> 01:13:55,305
Go see her for yourself.

854
01:14:43,785 --> 01:14:44,785
Ba Ra.

855
01:14:47,925 --> 01:14:49,025
This can't be happening.

856
01:14:57,765 --> 01:14:59,905
Do something. Don't just stand there.

857
01:15:04,705 --> 01:15:07,175
Ba Ra. Can you hear me?

858
01:15:09,605 --> 01:15:10,615
It's me, Ha Yong Joong.

859
01:15:11,245 --> 01:15:12,245
Geum Ba Ra.

860
01:15:19,255 --> 01:15:20,425
If you can hear me, squeeze my hand.

861
01:15:21,485 --> 01:15:22,485
Come on.

862
01:15:23,455 --> 01:15:24,455
It's me.

863
01:15:28,865 --> 01:15:30,665
Geum Ba Ra, you're stronger than anyone.

864
01:15:32,095 --> 01:15:33,095
Please.

865
01:15:44,815 --> 01:15:47,045
Hey. Are you just going to stand there?

866
01:15:49,515 --> 01:15:51,185
I'm moving her to Seoltap Hospital.

867
01:15:51,485 --> 01:15:52,485
It's no use.

868
01:15:52,485 --> 01:15:54,485
No use? After what you've done to her?

869
01:15:55,125 --> 01:15:56,955
You should've had Dr. Kim Jun Oh
do the surgery.

870
01:16:02,625 --> 01:16:04,495
Get Seoltap Hospital on the line.
It's an emergency.

871
01:16:04,595 --> 01:16:06,495
You want to drag her between hospitals
just to open up her skull again?

872
01:16:06,935 --> 01:16:08,635
One more surgery
and she'll die on the table.

873
01:16:17,915 --> 01:16:18,915
Then take responsibility.

874
01:16:24,955 --> 01:16:26,655
If you're human,
take responsibility for this, you bastard!

875
01:16:27,485 --> 01:16:28,485
Hey!

876
01:16:49,475 --> 01:16:51,345
I've made some beef porridge for you.

877
01:16:51,815 --> 01:16:54,885
I think I'm ready for a proper meal now.

878
01:17:36,425 --> 01:17:38,555
- Oh, yes...
- I'm Geum Ba Ra.

879
01:17:38,625 --> 01:17:40,465
That's right. You have a unique name.

880
01:17:42,965 --> 01:17:45,095
Why did you give up on me?
I'm your daughter.

881
01:17:49,905 --> 01:17:52,205
Shouldn't a mother recognize
her own child?

882
01:17:54,975 --> 01:17:56,405
After all the pain
of giving birth to me...

883
01:17:57,775 --> 01:17:58,775
(Director Shin)

884
01:18:08,125 --> 01:18:09,255
Yes, Director Shin.

885
01:18:17,465 --> 01:18:20,035
(Nua General Hospital)

886
01:18:48,825 --> 01:18:50,665
I never thought it would come to this.

887
01:20:00,165 --> 01:20:03,105
(Doctor Shin)

888
01:20:03,205 --> 01:20:04,835
You're supposed to wear a swimsuit
at the pool.

889
01:20:04,835 --> 01:20:06,535
Jin Ju's father came to see me.

890
01:20:06,635 --> 01:20:08,445
That looked like Geum Ba Ra, the reporter.

891
01:20:08,445 --> 01:20:10,375
Was she in a car accident or something?

892
01:20:10,445 --> 01:20:12,175
Is the owner of this house...

893
01:20:12,715 --> 01:20:14,085
still not out of the hospital yet?

894
01:20:14,085 --> 01:20:15,585
She's friends with my daughter.

895
01:20:15,645 --> 01:20:16,645
But you haven't heard?

896
01:20:17,285 --> 01:20:18,615
She passed away a little while ago.

897
01:20:20,355 --> 01:20:21,685
There won't be a funeral
before the burial.

898
01:20:21,885 --> 01:20:23,355
She was in the prime of her life.

899
01:20:23,425 --> 01:20:24,855
Your Daddy...

900
01:20:24,995 --> 01:20:26,455
cried so much today.

901
01:20:26,455 --> 01:20:27,565
Sounds just like Kim Jin Ju.

902
01:20:28,165 --> 01:20:29,795
It's true what they say,
people don't change.

903
01:20:31,765 --> 01:20:34,205
I'm not sure I'm supposed to address you.

904
01:20:34,205 --> 01:20:36,005
Let me get straight to the point.

905
01:20:36,105 --> 01:20:38,975
(Nua General Hospital)

906
01:20:39,035 --> 01:20:40,405
There's a dead body here!

907
01:20:40,745 --> 01:20:43,245
I think it's a patient
we operated on recently.

908
01:20:43,305 --> 01:20:44,675
- And the Director isn't here?
- No, sir.

909
01:20:44,875 --> 01:20:46,145
You are not going to believe this.

910
01:20:46,145 --> 01:20:47,885
I'm on my way to your house,
so run there...

911
01:20:47,885 --> 01:20:48,885
at the speed of light.

912
01:20:57,895 --> 01:20:59,895
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
